title: Halloween
overview: Fifteen years after murdering his sister on Halloween night 1963, Michael Myers escapes from a mental hospital and returns to the small town of Haddonfield, Illinois to kill again.

title: The Others
overview: A woman who lives in her darkened old family house with her two photosensitive children becomes convinced that the home is haunted.

title: Psycho
overview: A Phoenix secretary embezzles $40,000 from her employer's client, goes on the run, and checks into a remote motel run by a young man under the domination of his mother.

title: Get Out
overview: A young African-American visits his white girlfriend's parents for the weekend, where his simmering uneasiness about their reception of him eventually reaches a boiling point.

title: The Trial of the Chicago 7
overview: The story of 7 people on trial stemming from various charges surrounding the uprising at the 1968 Democratic National Convention in Chicago, Illinois.

title: The Manchurian Candidate
overview: A former prisoner of war is brainwashed as an unwitting assassin for an international Communist conspiracy.

title: The Silence of the Lambs
overview: A young F.B.I. cadet must receive the help of an incarcerated and manipulative cannibal killer to help catch another serial killer, a madman who skins his victims.

title: The Day of the Jackal
overview: A professional assassin codenamed "Jackal" plots to kill Charles de Gaulle, the President of France.

title: Shadow of a Doubt
overview: A young girl, overjoyed when her favorite uncle comes to visit the family, slowly begins to suspect that he is in fact the "Merry Widow" killer sought by the authorities.

title: Dial M for Murder
overview: A former tennis player tries to arrange his wife's murder after learning of her affair.

title: The Bourne Ultimatum
overview: Jason Bourne dodges a ruthless C.I.A. official and his Agents from a new assassination program while searching for the origins of his life as a trained killer.

title: Black Swan
overview: A committed dancer struggles to maintain her sanity after winning the lead role in a production of Tchaikovsky's "Swan Lake".

title: Saw
overview: Two strangers awaken in a room with no recollection of how they got there, and soon discover they're pawns in a deadly game perpetrated by a notorious serial killer.

title: The Usual Suspects
overview: A sole survivor tells of the twisty events leading up to a horrific gun battle on a boat, which began when five criminals met at a seemingly random police lineup.

title: North by Northwest
overview: A New York City advertising executive goes on the run after being mistaken for a government agent by a group of foreign spies.
stars: ['Cary Grant', 'Eva Marie Saint', 'James Mason', 'Jessie Royce Landis']

title: On the Waterfront
overview: An ex-prize fighter turned longshoreman struggles to stand up to his corrupt union bosses.

title: Bridge of Spies
overview: During the Cold War, an American lawyer is recruited to defend an arrested Soviet spy in court, and then help the CIA facilitate an exchange of the spy for the Soviet captured American U2 spy plane pilot, Francis Gary Powers.

title: No Country for Old Men
overview: Violence and mayhem ensue after a hunter stumbles upon a drug deal gone wrong and more than two million dollars in cash near the Rio Grande.

title: The Lady Vanishes
overview: While travelling in continental Europe, a rich young playgirl realizes that an elderly lady seems to have disappeared from the train.

title: The Imitation Game
overview: During World War II, the English mathematical genius Alan Turing tries to crack the German Enigma code with help from fellow mathematicians.
